Description: Atlis is a community for local recommendations.

Full Description: Atlis has digitized the word of mouth channel for local business referrals on a large scale.Highlights include: - Local search platforms using average star ratings are antiquated, creating a poor user experience, and causing significant harm to local business reputations. These products still live in the desktop era. - The system has removed negativity from the consumer feedback loop to prevent toxicity and abuse of local businesses, instead empowering satisfied customers to have a larger voice than ever before. - Atlis has taken the preferred channel of "friendly advice" and applied it to a city-wide audience, letting users ask each other for various local businesses, products, and services to receive suggestions directly in real-time. - Atlis tracks user preferences and collects a repository of the word-of-mouth advice across an entire city, making that dataset consumable via a passive search experience, as well. Machine learning will eventaully transform this the data collection into smart, personalized search results that knows what people would have suggested to you. - Company launched in NYC in October 2016 with its R&D team based in Tel Aviv. It has already built an engaged user base of over 10,000 and has signed up over 200 local businesses (without any B2B efforts). It has also secured valuable partnerships with Google, OpenTable, and others.

Description: Cardiovascular EMR Software Company
Headquarters Regions: Great Lakes, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Clinical Insight Systems, Inc. is an Electronic Medical Record (EMR) Software Company formed when it acquired the EMR product, Pronto, from the University of Rochester Medical Center (URMC).   Pronto was designed and developed by a team of leading cardiologists as an advanced clinical decision support EMR system and currently manages over 260,000 patient chart, saving clients millions of dollars a year while providing better patient care and delivering 2013 and 2015 ARRA "meaningful use" requirements today. Pronto is also in use at two other independent cardiology practices outside of the area.  Most EMR systems on the market today only mimic the paper based process. They provide the obvious benefits of an electronic chart, but little in the way of specialized decision support capabilities. Pronto has the ability to manually or automatically capture and store procedural test results and examination findings down to its finest level of detail. Pronto then uses this data to assist the physician in the assessment, analysis, and problem tracking that directly results in delivering more efficient and better patient care.  In addition, a very valuable structured research database is created as a byproduct of this process that can be used for research and outcomes analysis.  What makes Pronto really unique is that it not only captures procedural test results at the finest level of detail effortlessly, but it also provides an interpretation to the physician, for review, in the form of a clinical note that looks and sounds like a physician dictated it. Since Pronto knows what procedures were performed and the resulting diagnosis, it can easily assign the correct billing and diagnostic codes for reimbursement from 3rd party payers.
Industry Groups: Biotechnology, Health Care, Science and Engineering, Software

Full Description: LifeWorking Coworking is a hybrid coworking concept, blending corporate-grade ideation/collaboration-space with suburban locations to support clients ranging from  freelancers, to remote office workers and to corporate ideation teams – focusing on suburban “urbanizing “communities.  The Company’s ‘Community Innovation Hub’ concept is predicated on the following: Strong Suburban Economic Development/Community Engagement:  The Company identifies suburban communities focused on reinvigorating their Central Business District (CBD) with housing, retail and broader businesses and amenities that increase walkability, retain empty-nesters and attract older millennials.  The Company partners with those communities investing in Transit Oriented Development (TOD), and actively engage with their corporate constituents to drive this vision.  The Company will prioritize expansion into strategic landlord’s portfolios with an expectation that Retail Malls will comprise a material percentage of the pipeline. A Diverse Pipeline:  The Company’s expansion pipeline will include a mix of partnerships with opportunistic real estate investors, joint venture/partnerships and management service contracts aimed at aggressively expanding our network in capital efficient ways. Strategic Partnerships:  The Company views strategic partners not only as potential investors but as an opportunity to get on the inside of a portfolio to create capital-friendly joint ventures to drive our early growth and additional revenue streams. Description: P2P online e-commerce marketplace that allows individuals to list or rent just about anything. Its the AirBNB for your stuff.
Headquarters Regions: Tampa Bay Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Rentit is an adaptive, feature rich P2P app based marketplace that allows individuals to list and/or rent just about any physical item. From cold weather gear in Tahoe, to PaddleBoards in South Florida, there isn't anything you can't list on this platform. Need space to store some things for a few months? You can rent space on a shelf in someones garage. Have a family member or coworker visiting for a month and need an extra parking spot? Rentit allows that.  Our platform has integrated multiple delivery services to make it possible to create a request and have it delivered without having to leave your home. We also allow the option for you to store (pickup/dropoff) items in electronic lockers strategically placed across many metropolitan areas.  Through our proprietary RAPP (Rental Assurance Protection Plan), you can rest assure that your item is protected and cataloged prior to and after an item is rented. By allowing individuals to rent items that would typically stay in storage, or get thrown out, Rentit helps contribute to the overall health of the planet. Additionally, Rentit will allow crypto-currency to be used through the Coinbase API. As of this writing, there are 17 currencies (and counting) that lenders/renters will be able to utilize through our app. While not currently storing data on a Blockchain platform, a version in the near future created to help scale, will operate on one of the top blockchains.
